# CompassDocs reverse proxy — bootstrap configuration.
#
# You normally DON'T edit this file. The custom domain and HTTPS mode are
# configured from the web UI (Settings → Domain & HTTPS), and CompassDocs pushes
# the real configuration to Caddy's admin API at runtime.
#
# This file only provides the initial state on a brand-new container:
#   - the admin API listens on the Docker network so the app can reconfigure it
#   - the app is served over plain HTTP until a domain + TLS mode are saved
#
# Caddy is started with `--resume`, so after the first save it reloads the last
# applied configuration on restart; the app also re-applies it on boot.

{
	admin 0.0.0.0:2019
}

:80 {
	reverse_proxy app:3000
}
